    "These rules may include transaction amount thresholds, frequency of transactions, geographic locations, or unusual transaction patterns [3][4].",
    "Anomaly detection techniques, on the other hand, aim to identify outliers or deviations from normal behavior by analyzing statistical patterns in transaction data.",
    "These methods often involve calculating metrics such as mean, standard deviation, or z-scores to identify transactions that significantly differ from the norm.In contrast, machine learning approaches have gained popularity in credit fraud detection due to their ability to learn from data and adapt to evolving fraud patterns.",
    "Various machine learning algorithms, including decision trees, logistic regression, support vector machines, and neural networks, have been applied to this task.",
    "Decision trees can effectively capture complex decision boundaries and identify important features for classification."
